<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880408-0038 </DOCNO><HL> Sherwood Plans to Cut Costs </HL><SO> </SO><CO> SHD </CO><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Sherwood Group Inc., a securities firm, said it has instituted a major cost-cutting program and will reorganize its retail and wholesale market-making subsidiaries.    The moves come in light of trading losses and reduced revenue after October's stock-market crash, Sherwood said. </TEXT></DOC>